<li id="cite_note-laird-27"><span class="mw-cite-backlink noprint">↑ <sup><a href="#cite_ref-laird_27-0">a</a> et <a href="#cite_ref-laird_27-1">b</a></sup> </span><span class="reference-text"><abbr class="abbr indicateur-langue" title="Langue : anglais">(en)</abbr> Thomas Laird, <i>The Story of Tibet: Conversations with the Dalai Lama</i>, Grove Press, New York, 2007, <span class="nowrap"><abbr class="abbr" title="page">p.</abbr>&#160;266</span>; <span class="citation not_fr_quote" lang="en">«&#160;<span class="italique">When the search party reached us, the Dalai Lama said, "they said I spoke Lhasa dialect. I don't remember, but my mother told me that I spoke with the search party members in a language she didn't understand. So that means I used the language of my previous life."</span>&#160;»</span></span>
