<li id="cite_note-Harrer296-48"><span class="mw-cite-backlink noprint">↑ <sup><a href="#cite_ref-Harrer296_48-0">a</a> et <a href="#cite_ref-Harrer296_48-1">b</a></sup> </span><span class="reference-text">Heinrich Harrer, <i>Seven years in Tibet</i>, <abbr class="abbr nowrap italique" title="opere citato (« dans l&#39;ouvrage cité »)">op. cit.</abbr> , <span class="nowrap"><abbr class="abbr" title="page">p.</abbr>&#160;296</span>&#160;: <span class="citation not_fr_quote" lang="en">«&#160;<span class="italique">Lobsang had told me how quicktempered he had been as a child. No trace of this quality remained; in fact, he was really too collected and serious for his age.</span>&#160;»</span></span>
