<li id="cite_note-54"><span class="mw-cite-backlink noprint"><a href="#cite_ref-54">↑</a> </span><span class="reference-text">Henrich Harrer, <i>Seven years in Tibet</i>, translated from the German by Richard Graves; with an introduction by Peter Fleming; foreword by the Dalai Lama, E. P. Dutton, 1954&#160;: <span class="citation not_fr_quote" lang="en">«&#160;<span class="italique">He possessed an English work on the Second War in seven volumes, which he had translated into Tibetan. He knew how to distinguish between different types of airplane, automobiles, and tanks</span>&#160;»</span>.</span>
