<li id="cite_note-96"><span class="mw-cite-backlink noprint"><a href="#cite_ref-96">↑</a> </span><span class="reference-text"><abbr class="abbr indicateur-langue" title="Langue : anglais">(en)</abbr> Charles Hadfield, Jill Hadfield, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.fr/books?id=sXmgAAAAMAAJ&amp;q=%22New+Summer+Palace%22+Lhasa&amp;dq=%22New+Summer+Palace%22+Lhasa&amp;hl=fr&amp;sa=X&amp;redir_esc=y">‘’A Winter in Tibet’’</a>, Impact, 1988, 226 p., p. 30&#160;: <span class="citation not_fr_quote" lang="en">«&#160;<span class="italique">In the fifties, a new Summer Palace was built, an elegant two-story country house in mixed modern and Tibetan style.</span>&#160;»</span></span>
