<li id="cite_note-273"><span class="mw-cite-backlink noprint"><a href="#cite_ref-273">↑</a> </span><span class="reference-text"><abbr class="abbr indicateur-langue" title="Langue : anglais">(en)</abbr> Jonathan Mirsky, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.nybooks.com/daily/2013/04/09/cias-cancelled-war-tibet/">«&#160;Tibet&#160;: the CIA's Cancelled War&#160;»</a>, <i>The New York Review of Books</i>, 9 avril 2013&#160;: <span class="citation not_fr_quote" lang="en">«&#160;<span class="italique">According to Knaus, starting in the late 1950s, the Agency paid the Dalai Lama $15,000 a month. Those payments came to an end in 1974.</span>&#160;»</span></span>
